From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 19:50:50 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): add `runs prune` subcommand for safe run-dir
 cleanup (FR-E83)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add `flowai-workflow runs prune [--workflow <dir>] --keep <N> [--dry-run]`
which deletes the oldest run directories under `<workflowDir>/runs/` so the
N newest prunable runs remain. Run status and start time come solely from
replaying each run's `journal.jsonl` via the existing replayer.

Safety rules: never delete a run whose replayed status is non-terminal,
whose journal is missing/unreplayable (counts as non-terminal — keep when
in doubt), or that is referenced by `runs/.lock`; these are kept and
reported as skipped with a reason. `--keep` must be a non-negative integer
(clear error + non-zero exit otherwise). `--dry-run` deletes nothing.

Logic lives in `src/state/prune.ts` reusing `getRunDir`, the journal
replayer (`isTerminalStatus` now exported), and `defaultLockPath`/
`readLockInfo`; thin arg-parse + dispatch in `src/cli.ts`. Registers
FR-E83 in the SRS and documents the command in README.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
