+# `runs prune` — safe cleanup of old runs
+
+## Goal
+
+Add a `flowai-workflow runs prune` subcommand that deletes old run
+directories under `<workflowDir>/runs/` with strict, replay-grounded
+safety rules, so run-dir disk growth is bounded without ever destroying
+a live or unrecoverable run.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+A run's only durable record is its `journal.jsonl` (append-only recovery
+journal). Status and start time are obtained by replaying it with the
+existing replayer in `src/state/run-journal.ts` (`loadStateFromJournal`).
+A run directory without a replayable journal has unknown state by
+definition. The per-workflow run lock lives at `<workflowDir>/runs/.lock`
+(`src/state/lock.ts`).
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/cli.ts` dispatches `run` / `answer` / `init` / `mcp` subcommands
+  with hand-rolled arg parsing (no `runs` group yet).
+- `src/state/state.ts` exposes `getRunDir(runId, workflowDir)`.
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` exposes `replayRunJournal` /
+  `loadStateFromJournal`; `isTerminalStatus` is private.
+- `src/state/lock.ts` exposes `defaultLockPath` + `readLockInfo`.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- Follow the existing argument-parsing style in `src/cli.ts`; no new deps.
+- Reuse existing `src/state/` helpers for run-folder knowledge (run dir
+  path, journal replay, lock path/format) — no duplicated path
+  construction or replay logic.
+- Replayed status is one of `running | completed | failed | aborted`;
+  terminal = `completed | failed | aborted`. Anything else, plus a
+  missing/unreplayable journal, counts as NOT terminal (keep when in
+  doubt).
+- `deno task check` stays green.
+
+### Chosen semantics
+
+`--keep N` retains the `N` newest **prunable** runs (terminal AND
+unlocked). Non-terminal, unreplayable, and lock-referenced runs are
+**always** kept and reported as skipped with a reason — they do not
+consume `keep` slots (safety overrides the cap, per the explicit
+"regardless of `--keep`" rule). `--keep 0` therefore deletes every
+terminal unlocked run.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] (FR-E83, `src/state/prune_test.ts::… keeps N newest`, `deno task test`)
+  Keeps the N newest prunable runs, deletes the older ones.
+- [x] (FR-E83, `src/state/prune_test.ts::… skips non-terminal`, `deno task test`)
+  Never deletes a run whose replayed status is non-terminal.
+- [x] (FR-E83, `src/state/prune_test.ts::… skips locked`, `deno task test`)
+  Never deletes the run named by `runs/.lock`.
+- [x] (FR-E83, `src/state/prune_test.ts::… unreplayable`, `deno task test`)
+  Missing/unreplayable journal counts as non-terminal (skipped, kept).
+- [x] (FR-E83, `src/state/prune_test.ts::… keep 0`, `deno task test`)
+  `--keep 0` deletes all terminal unlocked runs.
+- [x] (FR-E83, `src/state/prune_test.ts::… dry-run`, `deno task test`)
+  `--dry-run` deletes nothing, exits 0, reports what would be deleted.
+- [x] (FR-E83, `src/state/prune_test.ts::… bad --keep rejected`, `deno task test`)
+  Non-negative-integer validation: bad `--keep` throws (non-zero exit).
+- [x] (FR-E83, `src/cli.ts --help`, `deno run -A src/cli.ts --help`)
+  Subcommand appears in CLI `--help`.
+- [x] (FR-E83, `documents/requirements-engine/06-distribution-and-housekeeping.md`,
+  `deno task check`) FR-E83 registered.
+
+## Solution
+
+Files:
+- **Create `src/state/prune.ts`** — pure-ish policy + executor:
+  - `classifyRuns(workflowDir)`: enumerate directory entries under
+    `getRunDir("", workflowDir)`'s parent (`<workflowDir>/runs/`); for
+    each subdirectory `runId` build a record. Read the lock once via
+    `readLockInfo(defaultLockPath(workflowDir))` (catch NotFound → no
+    locked run). For each run: if `runId === lockedRunId` →
+    `skip:locked`; else `loadStateFromJournal(getRunDir(runId,
+    workflowDir))` inside try/catch — on throw `skip:unreplayable`; on
+    non-terminal status `skip:nonterminal`; on terminal → prunable with
+    `startedAt`.
+  - `planPrune(records, keep)`: pure. Sort prunable by `startedAt` asc;
+    delete the oldest `max(0, prunable.length - keep)`, keep the rest;
+    skipped records pass through. Returns `{deleted, kept, skipped}`.
+  - `prune({workflowDir, keep, dryRun})`: classify → plan → if not
+    dryRun `Deno.remove(runDir, {recursive:true})` each deleted →
+    return `PruneResult`.
+  - `formatPruneSummary(result)`: two-level list (no tables) with
+    counts + per-skip reason.
+- **Edit `src/state/run-journal.ts`**: export `isTerminalStatus`
+  (reuse, don't duplicate the terminal definition).
+- **Edit `src/cli.ts`**:
+  - `parseRunsPruneArgs(args)`: `--workflow <dir>` (fallback
+    `resolveActiveWorkflow`), `--keep <N>` (mandatory; reject unless
+    `/^\d+$/`), `--dry-run`. Throw clear errors.
+  - `runRunsPrune(args)`: parse → resolve workflow → `prune(...)` →
+    print summary → `Deno.exit(0)`; catch → `console.error` +
+    `Deno.exit(1)`.
+  - Dispatch `runs` subcommand → require `prune` sub-subcommand.
+  - Add `runs prune` to `printUsage()`.
+- **Docs**: add FR-E83 to `06-distribution-and-housekeeping.md` and the
+  `requirements-engine.md` index map.
+
+Error handling: replay/IO errors per-run are caught and downgraded to
+`skip:unreplayable` (keep-when-in-doubt); arg-validation errors throw and
+exit non-zero; the lock-read NotFound is the only swallowed error (means
+"no lock").
+
+Verification: `deno task check`; `deno run -A src/cli.ts --help`;
+`deno run -A src/cli.ts runs prune --workflow .flowai-workflow/github-inbox --keep 5 --dry-run`.
+
+## Follow-ups
+
+- A separate `runs list`/inspection command (explicitly out of scope here).
